Dallas
comments: This was a promotional 45 RPM 7" released in advance of an anticipated album release.  The song was unsuccessful, and the album -- which also included "Dallas" -- was subsequently given only a limited release on 8-track in the United States under the artist name "Jimmie Dale Gilmore and The Flatlanders".  In 1997, the 8-track was inducted into The 8-Track Hall of Fame. In 1980, Charly reissued the recordings comprising the 8-track on LP as "One More Road", CRM 2038, under the artist name "The Flatlanders".  A truncated version of these recordings were also released under the artist name of "The Flatlanders" on CD as "More a Legend Than a Band".  The CD was released on the Rounder Select label in 1990, and bears UPC 011661553422.

comments: This version was again released in 1972 as part of the LP "Bukka White Sings Sic 'Em Dogs On Me" (Herwin, H 201). The album was by various artists, and the title of the song was given as "Sic 'Em Dogs On Me" -- adding the "Me" to the original title. In the track listing on the LP, Bukka is identified as "Washington (Barrelhouse) White". The Lomax recording has appeared on several mediums through the years -- under both titles. In addition, White recorded later versions of the song, which were released as "Sic' Em Dogs On" or "Sic' Em Dogs On Me".
